---
import ServiceCityPage from '~/components/pages/ServiceCityPage.astro';
import { services, cities } from '~/data/service-city-config';
---

<ServiceCityPage service={services['code-corrections']} city={cities['hudsonville-mi']}>
  <section class="container section-pad">
    <h2>Code Corrections in Hudsonville — Houses, Pole Barns, and Outbuildings</h2>
    <p>
      A Hudsonville property is rarely just a house. It's often a house plus a pole barn, a shop, or a detached garage
      on a feeder. That widens the code-correction conversation: detached-building sub-panels with neutrals improperly
      bonded to ground, missing equipment-grounding electrodes at the outbuilding, exposed NM-B running across the barn
      loft, and overloaded shop circuits without dedicated motor disconnects.
    </p>
    <p>
      For older homes on the residential side, the recurring findings are Federal Pacific or Zinsco panels still in
      service, ungrounded receptacles, and missing GFCI in basement and exterior locations. We document corrections in
      the packet your insurer needs. Often pairs with a <a href="/panel-upgrades-hudsonville-mi">panel upgrade</a> or
      <a href="/electrical-repairs-hudsonville-mi">broader repairs</a> when the underlying system is at its limit.
    </p>
  </section>
</ServiceCityPage>
